00:19:52.060 --> 00:19:54.460
to see what subset
of consumption items

00:19:54.460 --> 00:20:00.700
would best predict the total
in the socioeconomic survey.

00:20:00.700 --> 00:20:05.470
So that's kind of in the spirit
of Blundell and Pistaferri

00:20:05.470 --> 00:20:10.990
and so on in terms of taking
advantage, projecting to get

00:20:10.990 --> 00:20:13.305
something bigger than food.

00:20:13.305 --> 00:20:15.680
But actually there's some
interesting stuff with alcohol.

00:20:15.680 --> 00:20:17.920
I'll show you, if
I remember, when

00:20:17.920 --> 00:20:19.420
we get through these things.

00:20:19.420 --> 00:20:22.960
Income and production decisions
is another class of categories.

00:20:22.960 --> 00:20:25.090
We have assets and
income growth, even

00:20:25.090 --> 00:20:30.940
in the annual data, divided
into business, wage and salary,

00:20:30.940 --> 00:20:37.150
and agriculture and so on.

00:20:37.150 --> 00:20:40.970
And we see revenues
and expenses.

