And then we have a time fixed
effects and a household fixed

00:21:45.600 --> 00:21:48.660
effects, which are
estimated in the data.

00:21:54.690 --> 00:22:01.370
And here's the endogenous
variable being instrumented.

00:22:01.370 --> 00:22:03.490
And this is pretty simple.

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:08.550
And we also have those x
covariates here and time

00:22:08.550 --> 00:22:14.550
and household fixed effects for
household short-term credit,

00:22:14.550 --> 00:22:16.450
household and at date t.

00:22:16.450 --> 00:22:18.360
But we've also got
some dummies that

00:22:18.360 --> 00:22:23.447
kick in the first
year and second year

00:22:23.447 --> 00:22:24.280
of the intervention.

00:22:24.280 --> 00:22:26.370
Those are chis not x's.

00:22:26.370 --> 00:22:28.410
Those are 0, 1 variables.

00:22:28.410 --> 00:22:32.940
And they're interacted with the
inverse number of households.

00:22:32.940 --> 00:22:36.270
So inverse, that's just
