people's welfare

01:13:31.125 --> 01:13:34.820
in the model, not thinking
about cushion being administer,

01:13:34.820 --> 01:13:36.500
for instance.

01:13:36.500 --> 01:13:38.500
ROBERT TOWNSEND: Oh, yeah,
we're extracting away

01:13:38.500 --> 01:13:41.670
from the people who are
financing the programs.

01:13:41.670 --> 01:13:43.600
So there's all those
tax distortions

01:13:43.600 --> 01:13:45.430
being created to
generate the revenue

01:13:45.430 --> 01:13:48.675
to fund this program that aren't
involved in this calculation.

01:13:48.675 --> 01:13:50.050
AUDIENCE: Oh, I
was just thinking

01:13:50.050 --> 01:13:51.050
organizational capacity.

01:13:51.050 --> 01:13:54.260
So maybe one reason for
loaning to each village

01:13:54.260 --> 01:13:57.210
is that by head count, there's
be a lot more variation--

01:13:57.210 --> 01:13:58.210
ROBERT TOWNSEND: Maybe--

01:13:58.210 --> 01:13:59.914
AUDIENCE: Than a simple version.

01:14:02.670 --> 01:14:04.440
ROBERT TOWNSEND:
And then I just want

