First of all, what do
these coefficients mean?

01:14:15.630 --> 01:14:23.190
Well, you can think about
them as impact of the program.

01:14:23.190 --> 01:14:29.780
But that's kind of
like a funny number,

01:14:29.780 --> 01:14:33.730
because it's an average over
all these different people who

01:14:33.730 --> 01:14:36.430
got treated differently
and had different views

01:14:36.430 --> 01:14:38.380
about the program.

01:14:38.380 --> 01:14:43.240
So we're lucky in a way that
we saw this big salient number.

01:14:43.240 --> 01:14:47.260
And it helped us figure out a
model where something like that

01:14:47.260 --> 01:14:47.890
could happen.

01:14:47.890 --> 01:14:49.630
But then with that
model, we realize

01:14:49.630 --> 01:14:56.190
this number is not a uniform
benefit for all the households.

01:14:56.190 --> 01:14:58.580
So in other words,
a big advantage

01:14:58.580 --> 01:15:00.718
of a structural
model conditioned

